cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a deep neural network approach for mapping 2D pixel coordinates to RGB color values, which is a task commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the network's ability to encode images individually, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models for image processing is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the potential applications of the proposed approach in image resampling and completion, which are topics related to computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper includes experiments and results, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
